addtorow <- list()
addtorow$pos <- list(-1)
addtorow$command <-"\\multicolumn{3}{c}{Average real per capita GDP per quintile}\\\\"
T1 <- xtable(ans, align=c("l|cc"))
print(T1, add.to.row=addtorow, floating=FALSE)
@   
}
\end{center}  
\end{enumerate}
Using the information in the table, explain why the distribution of
the variable expressed in thousands of dollars is skewed while it is
not (or almost not) when it is expressed in logs.

